<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1191,2008]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,344,1299,1324]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" reason="1">Description.</emphasis>
Male (
<typeStatus box="[427,528,1300,1324]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">holotype</typeStatus>
) — Idiosoma L/W 488/352; integument very thin; dorsum with a circular postero-medial platelet. Coxal field corresponding to other species of the genus, L 228, Cx-III W 239; Cx-I medially separated, subcutaneous projections at caudal margin of Cx-I, medial margin of Cx-III and posterior part of medial margin of Cx-IV; Glandulae Limnesiae at centre of the medial margin of Cx-III; Cx-IV with one seta in area of insertion of IV-L. Genital field nearly circular, L/W 103/102, genital plates separated, Ac relatively small, Ac-2 smaller than Ac-1 and Ac-3, distance between Ac-1 and Ac-2 four to five times larger than between Ac-2 and Ac- 3, each genital plate with 5-6 setae, pre- and postgenital sclerite moderately developed, postgenital sclerite caudally not extending beyond genital plates. Palp (
<figureCitation box="[626,729,1551,1575]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1975,1998]" captionTargetBox="[161,1414,188,1945]" captionTargetId="figure-63@30.[151,1415,175,1961]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 21A–E. Limnesia diversipes sp. nov., IR15-2011 (A-C = holotype male, D-E = paratype female): A = genital and coxal field; B = IV-L-5 and -6; C = palp; D = palp (P-1 missing); E = chelicera. Scale bars = 100 µm." pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 21C</figureCitation>
): total L, 241; P-1, 14; P-2, 66; P-3, 45; P-4, 91; P-5, 25; L P-2/ P-4 ratio, 0.73; ventral seta of P-2 heavy, peg-shaped, inserting slightly laterally, ventral margin of P-4 with a long seta accompanied by a flat tubercle. Gnathosoma vL 92; chelicera total L 147. Legs: dL of I-L-3-6: 65, 66, 74, 92; dL of II-L-2-6: 55, 81, 87, 102, 112; II-L-6 dL/H ratio 3.1; sixth segment of I- and II-L sligtly modified (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1983,2006]" captionTargetBox="[162,1393,219,1956]" captionTargetId="figure-59@31.[151,1436,193,1982]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 22A–E. Limnesia diversipes sp. nov., IR15-2011 (B, D = holotype male, A, C, E = paratype female from IR15- 2011): A = genital field; B-C = I-L-5 and -6; D-E = II-L-4-6. Scale bars = 100 µm." pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Figs. 22B and -D</figureCitation>
), distally tapering, ventral margin with multiple irregular constrictions; dL of IV-L: 85, 71, 91, 120, 129, 128; IV-L-6 (
<figureCitation box="[299,399,1732,1756]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1975,1998]" captionTargetBox="[161,1414,188,1945]" captionTargetId="figure-63@30.[151,1415,175,1961]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 21A–E. Limnesia diversipes sp. nov., IR15-2011 (A-C = holotype male, D-E = paratype female): A = genital and coxal field; B = IV-L-5 and -6; C = palp; D = palp (P-1 missing); E = chelicera. Scale bars = 100 µm." pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 21B</figureCitation>
) with a strong sub-terminal seta, L 73.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1191,2008]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Female — Idiosoma L/W 553/442. Coxal field more slender than in male, L 273, Cx-III W 238. Genital field (
<figureCitation box="[159,261,1804,1828]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1983,2006]" captionTargetBox="[162,1393,219,1956]" captionTargetId="figure-59@31.[151,1436,193,1982]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 22A–E. Limnesia diversipes sp. nov., IR15-2011 (B, D = holotype male, A, C, E = paratype female from IR15- 2011): A = genital field; B-C = I-L-5 and -6; D-E = II-L-4-6. Scale bars = 100 µm." pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 22A</figureCitation>
) L/W 139/108, genital flap L 123, Ac-2 close to Ac-3, distance between Ac-1 and Ac-2 five to six times larger than between Ac-2 and Ac-3, each genital flap bearing three setae. Palp (
<figureCitation box="[1046,1151,1840,1864]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1975,1998]" captionTargetBox="[161,1414,188,1945]" captionTargetId="figure-63@30.[151,1415,175,1961]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 21A–E. Limnesia diversipes sp. nov., IR15-2011 (A-C = holotype male, D-E = paratype female): A = genital and coxal field; B = IV-L-5 and -6; C = palp; D = palp (P-1 missing); E = chelicera. Scale bars = 100 µm." pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 21D</figureCitation>
): dL: P-2, 77; P-3, 48; P- 4, 108; P-5, 28; L P-2/P-4 ratio, 0.71; palp as in male, but P-4 longer. Gnathosoma vL 124; chelicera (
<figureCitation box="[1327,1428,1876,1900]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1153,1176]" captionTargetBox="[167,1423,204,1116]" captionTargetId="figure-491@27.[151,1436,193,1133]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 19A–B. Neoatractides calidus sp. nov., paratype male, IR19-2011: A = dorsal shield; B = idiosoma, ventral view. Scale bar = 100 µm" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 19E</figureCitation>
) total L 179. Legs: dL of I-L-3-6: 62, 69, 77, 91; dL of II-L-2-6: 59, 69, 87, 108, 109; II-L-6 dL/H ratio 3.8; distal segments of I- and II-L unmodified, more slender than in male (
<figureCitation box="[860,1052,1948,1972]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1983,2006]" captionTargetBox="[162,1393,219,1956]" captionTargetId="figure-59@31.[151,1436,193,1982]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 22A–E. Limnesia diversipes sp. nov., IR15-2011 (B, D = holotype male, A, C, E = paratype female from IR15- 2011): A = genital field; B-C = I-L-5 and -6; D-E = II-L-4-6. Scale bars = 100 µm." pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Figs. 22C and -E</figureCitation>
); dL of IV-L: 92, 75, 96, 121, 140, 129; IV-L-6 subterminal seta L 76.
</paragraph>
